ies and the way they are stored in our minds. It goes beyond examining the morphological structure of words to examine the way words are spelt and the way they sound. At every stage, the book focuses not only on description, but also on the puzzles that words present. Supported by numerous examples, exercises, discussion questions, suggestions for further reading and a glossary, this is an accessible and lively guide to the linguistic study of English through the consideration of words.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish languagexLexicography. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447791840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474477918423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474477918/original  a978-3-11-078040-6  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles